Merge pull request #16 from PU-SDS/v1.0.5-beta

V1.0.5 beta

Vastly improved motif classification:
    The algorithm was completely rewritten.
    Now accurately classifies when number of variants are low.
Added the flag no_header_error to the cli. Now the exceptions should be more details inthe cli.

A few things related to header decoding:
1)  If no header format is provided WITH header decoding enabled, the exception NoHeaderFormat  is raised.
2)  If the header format provided by the user contains more header items than a given FASTA header, the exception
    HeaderItemCountInvalid is raised. With the current algorith we cannot decide which item is missing so we just
    let the user fit it themselves.
3)  If there is any empty items in the header (ex: >AIE52692.1 |Influenza A virus|Homo sapiens|), it will raised
    the exception HeaderItemEmpty UNLESS the new attribute `no_header_data_error` is set to True.  In this case all
    empty items are replaced with "Unknown"
Added new errorhandler for when header format not provided. Test added to validate this
Added test for empty sequences file
Added test for invalid kmer lengths
Fixed tests to work on linux environment (subprocess issue related to how linux understands args)

A few things:

1) HUNANA now checks if the FASTA file is empty, or invalid (if sequence count is 0)
2) Checks if the sequences are aligned (if all sequences are of equal length)
3) Checks if the kmer length is valid given the sequence length (if kmer length is bigger than, or seuql to sequence length)

All of these raise custom exceptions with detailed information to help the user as much as possible.
Updated requirements to download latest version
